1
00:00:00,031 --> 00:00:18,579
So this evening I thought we'd tackle what's known as the Four Great Elements.

2
00:00:19,807 --> 00:00:22,411
Actually, that's translating Mahabhuta.

3
00:00:23,112 --> 00:00:29,242
And Bhuta means being, so it should be properly translated as the four great beings.

4
00:00:29,263 --> 00:00:31,365
And this goes back to an earlier time.

5
00:00:31,847 --> 00:00:39,218
Well, it would have been believed in by people during the Buddha's time, maybe even today, who knows.

6
00:00:39,198 --> 00:00:42,643
That gods, of course, govern the universe.

7
00:00:42,883 --> 00:00:51,695
So, for instance, Agni, the fire god, he was the sun, but he actually governed the sun, governed the heat coming from the sun.

8
00:00:52,136 --> 00:00:58,945
So to appease him, if he got too hot, you'd have to do some rituals and do a bit of exorcism.

9
00:00:58,924 --> 00:01:23,346
few hymns you have to chant a few hymns and he was only second under the great under the under indra who was in charge of all the gods a bit like the greek zeus uh but by the time the buddha came along um they just become uh ordinary elements and they are earth water fire and oops i've lost my um

10
00:01:27,325 --> 00:01:28,266
I've lost my document.

11
00:01:30,430 --> 00:01:30,912
There we go.

12
00:01:31,352 --> 00:01:31,674
And they.

13
00:01:31,713 --> 00:01:34,459
Here we are.

14
00:01:34,478 --> 00:01:35,700
Dismissed.

15
00:01:35,721 --> 00:01:41,572
And they become just elements, just ordinary things that we can directly experience.

16
00:01:43,837 --> 00:01:48,186
Now, the great thing about these four elements is that they are self-produced.

17
00:01:48,266 --> 00:01:51,850
They cannot be reduced towards anything else.

18
00:01:51,870 --> 00:01:53,653
They're not derived from everything.

19
00:01:54,132 --> 00:02:07,867
So when we're experiencing these four great elements, earth, fire, water, and air, we're right at the base of our experience of life, our sensual experience of life, both outwardly and inwardly.

20
00:02:09,949 --> 00:02:17,277
And one of our aims in meditation is to get down to this level of insight, which we'll talk about in a bit.

21
00:02:18,557 --> 00:02:21,061
So what are these, what do they refer to?

22
00:02:21,181 --> 00:02:21,581
Okay.

23
00:02:21,882 --> 00:02:29,431
So now there's a discourse in the middle end saying number 28, given by Sariputta, not by the Buddha.

24
00:02:29,670 --> 00:02:41,064
Sariputta, remember, was called the general of the Dharma by the Buddha, because he was second only to understanding the Dharma itself.

25
00:02:41,786 --> 00:02:45,509
So he's understood to have really grasped the truth of things.

26
00:02:47,431 --> 00:02:48,532
And this is what it says.

27
00:02:49,252 --> 00:02:53,938
So Earth element represents solidity, structure.

28
00:02:54,939 --> 00:03:07,836
Now, this it's interesting because I read a physicist who was saying that there was no such thing as space, but that matter or subatomic energy created it.

29
00:03:07,816 --> 00:03:12,484
space came because matter itself had arrived.

30
00:03:12,963 --> 00:03:19,634
So it wasn't a case of matter going into an empty place that we call space.

31
00:03:20,316 --> 00:03:22,901
The space was being created by matter itself.

32
00:03:23,481 --> 00:03:27,687
And there's a hint of that in the Buddha's teachings, but it is only a hint.

33
00:03:27,949 --> 00:03:30,532
It just might be me.

34
00:03:32,251 --> 00:03:39,400
So it includes hardness, but it also softness, and it's associated with form, occupies space.

35
00:03:39,760 --> 00:03:42,563
Okay, so this is what it includes in the body.

36
00:03:42,584 --> 00:03:52,676
Head hair, body hair, nails, teeth, skin, flesh, sinews, bones, bone marrow, kidneys, heart, liver, and there's a whole load of stuff, right?

37
00:03:53,258 --> 00:03:58,764
But the important thing is that this is internal, pertaining to an individual.

38
00:03:59,639 --> 00:04:02,675
And then Sariputta makes this statement.

39
00:04:03,016 --> 00:04:05,751
This is called the interior earth element.

40
00:04:06,524 --> 00:04:15,019
The interior earth element and the exterior earth element are just the earth element.

41
00:04:15,159 --> 00:04:16,862
So in other words, you can't get beyond that.

42
00:04:17,463 --> 00:04:23,855
So it's a bit like, for instance, in physics, once we're down to subatomic energy and particles, that's it.

43
00:04:23,915 --> 00:04:25,639
You can't get beneath that.

44
00:04:26,038 --> 00:04:30,286
That's what everything is made of, we could say.

45
00:04:32,208 --> 00:04:34,716
Okay, so the same happens with water element.

46
00:04:34,735 --> 00:04:40,132
So the water element is what is cohesive, fluidity, elasticity.

47
00:04:40,634 --> 00:04:44,225
Yeah, that sort of feeling about things.

48
00:04:44,391 --> 00:04:47,476
And it's liquid in the body, of course.

49
00:04:47,716 --> 00:04:52,002
So he says the water elements may be interior or exterior.

50
00:04:52,644 --> 00:04:54,646
And what is the interior water element?

51
00:04:55,389 --> 00:05:02,079
Anything that is water, watery and appropriated that's internal pertaining to an individual.

52
00:05:02,098 --> 00:05:08,528
It includes bile, phlegm, pus, blood, sweat, fat, tears and all the rest of it.

53
00:05:08,949 --> 00:05:09,689
So...

54
00:05:09,670 --> 00:05:13,636
So it's not as though we're short of the water element in the body.

55
00:05:14,076 --> 00:05:15,658
In fact, I think we're mostly water.

56
00:05:18,122 --> 00:05:21,107
So then again, it finishes with that phrase.

57
00:05:21,187 --> 00:05:23,511
This is called the interior water element.

58
00:05:24,110 --> 00:05:30,420
The interior water element and the exterior water element are just the water element.

59
00:05:31,942 --> 00:05:33,906
So then he talks about fire.

60
00:05:34,814 --> 00:05:39,785
So this is, of course, warmth, the metabolic processes.

61
00:05:39,805 --> 00:05:42,170
And it also means the process of aging.

62
00:05:42,571 --> 00:05:43,271
That's interesting.

63
00:05:44,615 --> 00:05:47,682
So the fire element may be interior or exterior.

64
00:05:48,062 --> 00:05:50,127
And what is the interior fire element?

65
00:05:50,447 --> 00:05:52,451
Anything that's fire or fiery.

66
00:05:52,987 --> 00:05:57,636
and appropriated, that's internal, pertaining to an individual.

67
00:05:57,656 --> 00:06:16,987
This includes that which warms, that which ages, that which heats you up when feverish, that which properly digests food and drink, and anything else that is fire, fiery, and appropriated, that's internal, pertaining to an individual.

68
00:06:17,423 --> 00:06:19,925
This is called the interior fire element.

69
00:06:20,387 --> 00:06:26,656
The interior fire element and the exterior fire element are just the fire element.

70
00:06:29,399 --> 00:06:33,685
And the final one is, of course, air, sometimes translated as wind.

71
00:06:33,704 --> 00:06:38,031
It's to do with movement and it's opposite of being still.

72
00:06:39,040 --> 00:06:40,862
And what is the air element?

73
00:06:41,223 --> 00:06:44,269
The air element may be interior or exterior.

74
00:06:44,930 --> 00:06:47,153
And what is the interior air element?

75
00:06:47,694 --> 00:06:55,208
Anything that is air or wind, yeah, and appropriated, that's internal, pertaining to an individual.

76
00:06:55,228 --> 00:07:04,204
This includes winds that go up and down, winds in the belly or the bowels, winds that flow through the limbs in breath and out breath.

77
00:07:04,858 --> 00:07:12,466
Now that winds that flow through the limbs, I think that's referring to prana, right?

78
00:07:12,487 --> 00:07:14,427
The energy that's within the body.

79
00:07:17,771 --> 00:07:22,235
And so the winds include both literal gas and movements of energy.

80
00:07:23,336 --> 00:07:25,658
This is called the interior air element.

81
00:07:25,939 --> 00:07:32,685
The interior air element and the exterior air element are just the air element.

82
00:07:33,047 --> 00:07:33,346
Okay.

83
00:07:34,492 --> 00:07:50,730
Now, at the end of all those four elements, there's a refrain, and I've left it out because it's an important little bit to understand, because this is why we are investigating the four elements.

84
00:07:52,512 --> 00:07:55,956
This should be truly seen with right understanding like this.

85
00:07:56,576 --> 00:08:01,663
This is not mine, I am not this, and this is not myself.

86
00:08:02,555 --> 00:08:14,447
When you truly see with right understanding, when you truly see this with right understanding, you reject the air element, detaching awareness from the air element, okay?

87
00:08:15,007 --> 00:08:27,819
So in other words, when we're actually experiencing this, there's a moment of reflection where we can say to ourself, well, look, that is not me, it's not mine, and it is not myself.

88
00:08:27,800 --> 00:08:34,870
And in so doing, we're sort of separating what it is that's actually thinking that, that's actually saying that.

89
00:08:35,410 --> 00:08:38,335
And that's, of course, your intuitive awareness.

90
00:08:40,116 --> 00:08:46,586
And although Sariputta doesn't mention it here, it's at that level that you can see impermanence.

91
00:08:46,726 --> 00:08:50,030
You can see the changing nature of things much more easily.

92
00:08:51,833 --> 00:08:54,076
We'll come to that again in a little bit.

93
00:08:55,913 --> 00:08:59,279
So we can see now why they're used as meditation objects.

94
00:09:00,201 --> 00:09:04,691
In order to get down to that level of experience, you've got to focus in on it.

95
00:09:05,373 --> 00:09:08,600
So it's very good for getting the mind to be very still and focused.

96
00:09:08,980 --> 00:09:12,167
And of course, what's driving it is your interest.

97
00:09:12,366 --> 00:09:17,993
Remember that the whole process of investigation is the process of liberation.

98
00:09:18,033 --> 00:09:21,476
We're not taking anything on faith.

99
00:09:21,996 --> 00:09:23,558
We don't have to believe anything.

100
00:09:23,918 --> 00:09:30,546
And that, in fact, will be a hindrance because everything that the Buddha is putting to us is to be investigated.

101
00:09:31,988 --> 00:09:34,870
OK, so it helps with the concentration.

102
00:09:36,272 --> 00:09:36,972
And

103
00:09:37,966 --> 00:09:42,052
What we're trying to understand, apart from that, is how we construct the world.

104
00:09:42,514 --> 00:09:45,057
And we'll come to that a little bit more down the line.

105
00:09:49,044 --> 00:09:50,226
Okay.

106
00:09:50,248 --> 00:09:52,631
And in that way, we're developing this insight, right?

107
00:09:52,672 --> 00:09:54,033
The insight of vipassana.

108
00:09:54,094 --> 00:09:56,138
So it's a process of seeing things as they are.

109
00:09:58,241 --> 00:10:01,947
So, if we take an example now.

110
00:10:03,261 --> 00:10:07,368
If we take an example, an easy one, say of pain or discomfort.

111
00:10:08,349 --> 00:10:18,964
So as soon as that feeling of pain arises and we become aware of it, the first port of call, remember, is to see how we're reacting to it.

112
00:10:20,024 --> 00:10:21,868
So we want to move, we want to get rid of it.

113
00:10:22,128 --> 00:10:23,129
So that's the first thing.

114
00:10:23,890 --> 00:10:28,256
And we wait, we have to wait until that reaction begins to fade away.

115
00:10:29,215 --> 00:10:34,546
Then we can feel the pain more equanimously, patiently, right?

116
00:10:34,566 --> 00:10:36,048
So we can just be with the pain.

117
00:10:37,091 --> 00:10:43,043
And our noting word, our reflection on it is that this is pain and we can still do the same thing.

118
00:10:43,163 --> 00:10:47,452
We can say, this is not me, not mine, not myself.

119
00:10:47,472 --> 00:10:49,738
You can actually say things like that to yourself, yeah?

120
00:10:51,000 --> 00:11:00,995
And then once that's very clear to you and it's distanced from the awareness, like it's a real object, that's when you can plunge into the object, right?

121
00:11:01,014 --> 00:11:05,780
So this is a phrase that my teacher Sayadaw Upandita would often say.

122
00:11:06,322 --> 00:11:14,393
And it actually is trying to express what the Buddha says in the discourse on how to establish right awareness.

123
00:11:14,373 --> 00:11:19,940
He uses a form which translates as to feel feelings in feelings.

124
00:11:20,299 --> 00:11:21,341
That's what he says, right?

125
00:11:21,761 --> 00:11:24,043
To feel the body in the body.

126
00:11:24,745 --> 00:11:36,499
So he was having problems getting across to people, to his students, that you have to get into things, you have to sink into the object.

127
00:11:37,288 --> 00:11:38,431
So here you are.

128
00:11:38,451 --> 00:11:39,331
You see the pain.

129
00:11:39,753 --> 00:11:45,240
So you then sink into that pain with the intention of seeing what it's made of.

130
00:11:45,341 --> 00:11:49,908
In other words, you're deconstructing that experience.

131
00:11:49,927 --> 00:11:55,176
And what we discover, of course, is things like heat, pressure and so on.

132
00:11:55,456 --> 00:11:57,580
Little different words will come to mind.

133
00:11:58,601 --> 00:12:00,764
And when that's clear.

134
00:12:01,032 --> 00:12:03,615
and distanced, and it's quite clearly an object.

135
00:12:03,835 --> 00:12:08,279
You can always say to yourself, look, that's not me, not mine, and not myself.

136
00:12:08,961 --> 00:12:09,201
Okay?

137
00:12:10,442 --> 00:12:20,933
And then you recognize that when you come to the next level of perception, which gives these sensations meaning, the word pain arises.

138
00:12:21,575 --> 00:12:25,479
Ah, so now we know that pain is a mental construct.

139
00:12:25,538 --> 00:12:27,041
It doesn't actually exist.

140
00:12:27,520 --> 00:12:30,684
What actually exists are these sensations.

141
00:12:31,356 --> 00:12:36,625
And now it doesn't mean to say that you can forget what pain is.

142
00:12:36,725 --> 00:12:38,489
You need to know when to go to the doctor.

143
00:12:39,070 --> 00:12:43,116
But now we know that pain is a mental construct.

144
00:12:44,097 --> 00:12:48,184
And then the third level is to see our relationship to pain.

145
00:12:49,006 --> 00:12:55,136
And that's when we have that growth of patience and forbearance with what is unpleasant.

146
00:12:55,976 --> 00:13:03,777
So there's a whole process there, which is just part of that vipassana insight process.

147
00:13:07,198 --> 00:13:13,787
So, yes, and just finally, in daily life, you can always bring it to mind.

148
00:13:13,886 --> 00:13:14,648
It's very simple.

149
00:13:14,687 --> 00:13:16,028
You're sitting at a table.

150
00:13:16,068 --> 00:13:18,792
You pick up your knife and fork or a spoon.

151
00:13:19,373 --> 00:13:28,562
And just for the moment there, just recognize that there's a feeling of the steel, you know, the sense of maybe coldness.

152
00:13:28,943 --> 00:13:36,091
The cutlery might be cold or you might sense the hardness of it.

153
00:13:36,932 --> 00:13:52,556
When you're drinking a tea or coffee or just a juice or something, just for a moment to feel that liquidity, the way that the liquid is moving around in the mouth.

154
00:13:52,576 --> 00:14:00,246
When you're outside, occasionally this summer, you might feel the warmth of the sun, at least in the UK.

155
00:14:00,687 --> 00:14:01,929
You'll be very lucky these days.

156
00:14:02,490 --> 00:14:06,096
And you can feel the warmth of the sun on your skin.

157
00:14:06,447 --> 00:14:12,775
When walking, you get that feeling of movement, the body moving through space, you might say.

158
00:14:14,077 --> 00:14:17,462
So these things we can actually experience.

159
00:14:17,823 --> 00:14:23,272
You can also see it on a sort of second hand, like the trees moving with the wind and so on.

160
00:14:26,015 --> 00:14:34,969
And it's just this constant recognition that everything that we're experiencing at a physical level is based on these four elements.

161
00:14:35,624 --> 00:14:53,855
Now, I must say that when it comes to the more animal elements of smelling and tasting, there's no real understanding as to what creates the various subjective tastes within the mouth of sweetness, sour, salty, all those sorts of things.

162
00:14:55,837 --> 00:14:56,940
But...

163
00:14:58,236 --> 00:15:01,379
It's like the photons that hit the eye.

164
00:15:01,419 --> 00:15:03,423
That would be seen as a fire element.

165
00:15:04,202 --> 00:15:08,168
But what the eye actually sees are all these very different shapes and colors.

166
00:15:08,587 --> 00:15:12,312
But it's still at the base of the eye, just a fire element.

167
00:15:13,072 --> 00:15:17,717
And in the same with the ear, all we're getting is pressure waves.

168
00:15:17,738 --> 00:15:21,322
And that's all that's actually being picked up by the sense base.

169
00:15:21,341 --> 00:15:24,304
And you can actually experience that, that there's no sound.

170
00:15:24,384 --> 00:15:27,248
It's just a sensation of touch.

171
00:15:27,312 --> 00:15:36,280
And then that enters into the mind, and it's the mind which turns it into a recognizable sound.

172
00:15:36,301 --> 00:15:40,946
Okay.

173
00:15:42,967 --> 00:15:46,412
So, okay, we're going to do a little exercise, right?

174
00:15:46,432 --> 00:15:47,932
And then we'll sit for a while.

175
00:15:49,434 --> 00:15:57,082
So if we sit comfortably and just close our eyes a little, and I'll just mention some parts of the body that you can contact.

176
00:15:58,447 --> 00:16:02,493
according to these four elements, okay?

177
00:16:03,153 --> 00:16:09,583
So we're just sitting there quietly, and we want to find something which is hard.

178
00:16:10,043 --> 00:16:26,749
So it could be that your one thumb is feeling the hardness of a nail, or you could be having your hand on your knee, just the kneecap there, and just get a feel of the hardness of it.

179
00:16:28,365 --> 00:16:44,326
Now, at this point, we can just say to ourselves, well, you see, that's not me, it's not mine, and it's not myself.

180
00:16:48,029 --> 00:16:58,102
Now, the hardness you're feeling, I suppose it's better in the knee, really, if you can, is to feel it on the bone or in the bone, not in the finger itself.

181
00:16:58,875 --> 00:16:59,798
That's a bit difficult.

182
00:17:17,346 --> 00:17:19,169
You can, of course, feel it on the finger.

183
00:17:19,529 --> 00:17:20,951
That's not a problem either.

184
00:17:25,690 --> 00:17:35,442
And then if we try to find something which is warm or cool, the heat of the body, perhaps you can feel a part of the body that's warm.

185
00:17:36,944 --> 00:17:46,699
Or it could be if you put one hand on the back of the other hand, you might find that the fingers are cooler and you can feel that there's a change of temperature there.

186
00:17:47,759 --> 00:17:49,722
And the palm of the hand being warmer.

187
00:17:53,298 --> 00:17:57,031
and just get into that feeling of warmth or coolness.

188
00:17:58,738 --> 00:18:03,695
So at the moment I can feel the coolness of my fingers and the warmth of my palm.

189
00:18:25,816 --> 00:18:31,121
And I can also feel how the energy is moving.

190
00:18:31,201 --> 00:18:34,944
The palm feels cooler and the fingers are beginning to feel warmer.

191
00:18:40,490 --> 00:18:43,673
I'm right there at the base of my experience.

192
00:18:46,195 --> 00:18:48,178
And then the next one would be liquidity.

193
00:18:48,278 --> 00:18:51,621
So you can fill your mouth with a little saliva.

194
00:19:03,413 --> 00:19:15,388
There's also you can squeeze a muscle of your thigh or your biceps or whatever, or a muscle in the hand, the muscle at the thumb.

195
00:19:16,109 --> 00:19:21,657
And just as you as you press it, you can feel it sort of squeezing us that way.

196
00:19:32,674 --> 00:19:38,103
And then finally, there's movement.

197
00:19:38,123 --> 00:19:43,570
So we can make that very simple by just lifting your hand and placing it back onto your knee.

198
00:19:46,114 --> 00:19:52,303
Or observing the falling and rising of the breath in the body, the chest, the stomach or the abdomen.

199
00:19:57,852 --> 00:20:03,280
And all you're trying to be aware of, to get down to, is that feeling of just movement.

200
00:20:05,144 --> 00:20:07,907
That's more easily done when it's neutral.

201
00:20:17,223 --> 00:20:22,392
And again, you can say to yourself, this is not me, not mine, and not myself.

202
00:20:34,386 --> 00:20:36,829
Okay, so that's a sort of quick introduction.

203
00:20:37,611 --> 00:20:42,698
The last thing is that, of course, you can also do this with your emotional life.

204
00:20:43,138 --> 00:20:44,760
An obvious one would be anger.

205
00:20:44,840 --> 00:20:48,006
If you feel a bit angry about something, irritated about something.

206
00:20:48,807 --> 00:20:55,055
So when you come off the fantasy and you come into the body, then you feel, first of all, that there is anger.

207
00:20:55,195 --> 00:21:02,705
But as you go into the anger, there is just this energy, just heat that's going on and movement, heat movement mainly.

208
00:21:03,007 --> 00:21:11,423
So it's just deconstructing what we're actually experiencing, always taking away that sense of something being substantial, being real.

209
00:21:11,482 --> 00:21:17,134
And that's how we use these four great elements.

210
00:21:20,557 --> 00:21:21,137
Very good.

211
00:21:21,519 --> 00:21:36,067
I can only hope my words have been of some assistance, that I have not caused confusion, and that by your careful investigation of the four elements, you will liberate yourself from all suffering sooner rather than later.

